{"title":"M1 2 Protocolo BLUE iPad","guid":"","filepath":"/Users/criaah/Vault/📚 Resources/Mapas-Mentales/Entidades clínicas/General/M1 2 Protocolo BLUE iPad.smmx","root":{"id":"0","parent":"-1","text":"MODULO 1.2 —\\NPROTOCOLO BLUE\\N(Bedside Lung Ultrasound\\Nin Emergency)","guid":"b96o5XNrEmF0--j1_UbGIg","children":[{"id":"1","parent":"0","text":"PRERREQUISITOS","guid":"","children":[{"id":"2","parent":"1","text":"→ M1.1 Semiología pulmonar normal (signos básicos)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"3","parent":"1","text":"Dominio\\NOBLIGATORIO\\Nde","guid":"9GvQEi1K9iKpEtK4DeVDDw","children":[{"id":"4","parent":"3","text":"§ Deslizamiento pleural [definido M1.1]","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"5","parent":"3","text":"§ Líneas A [definido M0.5/M1.1]","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"6","parent":"3","text":"§ Líneas B [definido M0.5/M1.1]","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"7","parent":"3","text":"Consolidación alveolar","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"8","parent":"3","text":"Derrame pleural (signo del quad, signo del sinusoide)","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"9","parent":"0","text":"CONECTA CON","guid":"","children":[{"id":"10","parent":"9","text":"→ M1.3 Derrame pleural (PLAPS como hallazgo BLUE)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"11","parent":"9","text":"→ M1.4 Consolidación vs atelectasia (perfil C, broncograma aéreo dinámico)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"12","parent":"9","text":"→ M1.5 Neumotórax (perfil A sin sliding + lung point)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"13","parent":"9","text":"→ M4.2 RUSH tanque (BLUE integrado en evaluación del shock)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"14","parent":"9","text":"→ M11.1 Protocolo integrativo BLUE (aplicación completa)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"15","parent":"9","text":"→ M11.4 FALLS protocol (derivado directo del BLUE)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"16","parent":"0","text":"GLOSARIO APLICABLE","guid":"","children":[{"id":"17","parent":"16","text":"§ Líneas A [definido M0.5/M1.1] → perfil normal aireado","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"18","parent":"16","text":"§ Líneas B [definido M0.5/M1.1] → interstitial syndrome","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"19","parent":"16","text":"§ Deslizamiento pleural [definido M1.1] → presente/abolido","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"20","parent":"16","text":"§ Lung point [definido M1.5] → pneumothorax","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"21","parent":"16","text":"§ FEVI eyeball [definido M2.2] → complemento diagnóstico","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"22","parent":"16","text":"§ VCI [definido M2.5] → complemento volemico","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"23","parent":"16","text":"§ Compresibilidad venosa [definido M6.1] → componente venoso BLUE","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"24","parent":"0","text":"CONTEXTO Y\\NFUNDAMENTO","guid":"P9y-1i6ZPmK3J29_-3DF1w","children":[{"id":"25","parent":"24","text":"Lichtenstein DA, Mezière GA → Chest 2008;134(1):117-125","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"26","parent":"24","text":"Estudio observacional → 301 consecutivos, 260 incluidos → UCI Francia","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"27","parent":"24","text":"Insuficiencia respiratoria aguda (IRA) → diagnóstico inmediato al ingreso","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"28","parent":"24","text":"CONCEPTO CENTRAL → eco pulmonar como gold standard a la cabecera","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"29","parent":"24","text":"Precisión diagnóstica global → 90.5% (derivación, no validación)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"30","parent":"24","text":"Ventaja principal → VELOCIDAD diagnostica → <3 minutos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"31","parent":"24","text":"No requiere Doppler ni ecocardiografía completa","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"32","parent":"24","text":"Requiere SOLO un transductor microconvexo (ideal) o convexo pequeño","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"33","parent":"24","text":"Complementado con análisis venoso (TVP) → componente integrado","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"34","parent":"0","text":"TRES ITEMS\\NEVALUADOS","guid":"h_P9tPGGLUaRdTbpKeuZwA","children":[{"id":"35","parent":"34","text":"ARTEFACTOS","guid":"","children":[{"id":"36","parent":"35","text":"Líneas A predominantes → aire subpleural normal o patológico","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"37","parent":"35","text":"Líneas B difusas anteriores → síndrome intersticial","guid":"","children":[{"id":"38","parent":"37","text":"B+ → 3 o más líneas B en una ventana → patológico","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"39","parent":"34","text":"DESLIZAMIENTO\\NPLEURAL","guid":"Y9h8c9H7CJLMSFMdFcBPCA","children":[{"id":"40","parent":"39","text":"Presente → descarta neumotórax en esa zona","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"41","parent":"39","text":"Abolido → orienta a neumotórax, adherencias, apnea [→ M1.1]","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"42","parent":"34","text":"CONSOLIDACION\\NY/O DERRAME","guid":"Xv1BR89DMBoJDtqHUV4zvA","children":[{"id":"43","parent":"42","text":"Consolidación anterior → perfil C","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"44","parent":"42","text":"PLAPS (Posterolateral Alveolar\\Nand/or Pleural Syndrome)","guid":"VnSiizstBKDlJBpbLlcXfw","children":[{"id":"45","parent":"44","text":"Consolidación y/o derrame en zona posterolateral","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"46","parent":"44","text":"Evaluación en decúbito semisupino → sonda pequeña posterior","guid":"","children":[]}]}]}]},{"id":"47","parent":"0","text":"ZONAS DE\\NEXPLORACIÓN\\N(BLUE-points)","guid":"4l5l3ZhqF--YrPfanS_ONA","children":[{"id":"48","parent":"47","text":"STAGE 1 → zona anterior (zona 1)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"49","parent":"48","text":"Pared torácica anterior → paciente supino o semi-sentado","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"50","parent":"48","text":"Dividida en superior e inferior","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"51","parent":"47","text":"STAGE 2 → zona lateral (zona 2)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"52","parent":"51","text":"Pared lateral → agrega información","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"53","parent":"47","text":"STAGE 3 → zona posterolateral (zona 3)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"54","parent":"53","text":"Sonda pequeña → mínimo desplazamiento del paciente","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"55","parent":"53","text":"PLAPS-point → zona clave para neumonía y derrame","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"56","parent":"47","text":"CADA PARED dividida en mitad superior e inferior","guid":"","children":[{"id":"57","parent":"56","text":"Total → 6 áreas de investigación por hemitórax","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"58","parent":"47","text":"BLUE-POINTS SIMPLIFICADOS (3\\Npuntos estandarizados)","guid":"zB2J6fszbJ8KSMbqvKyPyw","children":[{"id":"59","parent":"58","text":"Upper BLUE-point → pared anterior superior","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"60","parent":"58","text":"Lower BLUE-point → pared anterior inferior","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"61","parent":"58","text":"PLAPS-point → posterolateral","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"62","parent":"58","text":"Ref: Lichtenstein D. The BLUE-points. Crit Ultrasound J. 2011;3:109-110","guid":"oTf_3b06O69D69rfQEPxCw","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"63","parent":"0","text":"PERFILES ECOGRÁFICOS\\N(BLUE profiles)","guid":"74KUBpZGLU0N4FzziaxkpQ","children":[{"id":"64","parent":"63","text":"PERFIL A\\N(A-profile)","guid":"gnbHq3yJxSlcPrMDLNHtBQ","children":[{"id":"65","parent":"64","text":"Líneas A predominantes anteriores + deslizamiento pleural presente","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"66","parent":"64","text":"Stage 1/1' → zona anterior bilateral","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"67","parent":"64","text":"SUGIERE","guid":"","children":[{"id":"68","parent":"67","text":"EPOC exacerbado","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"69","parent":"67","text":"Asma","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"70","parent":"67","text":"Tromboembolismo pulmonar (si TVP+)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"71","parent":"67","text":"Neumonía posterior (si PLAPS+)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"72","parent":"64","text":"DESCARTA CASI con certeza → edema pulmonar cardiogénico","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"73","parent":"64","text":"Rendimiento EPOC/asma → S 89%, E 97%","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"74","parent":"63","text":"PERFIL B\\N(B-profile)","guid":"cp-YULgBqHtbEj4nhGlPvQ","children":[{"id":"75","parent":"74","text":"Líneas B+ difusas bilaterales anteriores + deslizamiento pleural presente","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"76","parent":"74","text":"HOMOGÉNEO → bilateral simétrico","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"77","parent":"74","text":"SUGIERE → EDEMA PULMONAR CARDIOGÉNICO","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"78","parent":"74","text":"Rendimiento → S 97%, E 95%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"79","parent":"74","text":"DESCARTA CASI → EPOC, TEP, neumotórax","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"80","parent":"74","text":"⭐ Perfil B = diagnóstico más rápido → <1 minuto","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"81","parent":"63","text":"PERFIL B'\\N(B'-profile)","guid":"yc3tKdjID6Y241zDt9lSKQ","children":[{"id":"82","parent":"81","text":"Líneas B+ difusas + deslizamiento pleural ABOLIDO","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"83","parent":"81","text":"SUGIERE → neumonía (patrón bilateral)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"84","parent":"81","text":"Diferencia con B-profile → abolición del sliding","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"85","parent":"81","text":"También pensar → SDRA vs edema si contexto clínico [→ M1.6]","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"86","parent":"63","text":"PERFIL A/B\\N(A/B-profile)","guid":"JrPqsMxZAUpNTL8bbA8aNA","children":[{"id":"87","parent":"86","text":"ASIMÉTRICO → líneas B masivas en un lado, líneas A en el otro","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"88","parent":"86","text":"SUGIERE → NEUMONÍA (unilateral)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"89","parent":"86","text":"Alta especificidad para proceso neumónico","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"90","parent":"63","text":"PERFIL C\\N(C-profile)","guid":"xswa21L2XnT62LT_BLhizQ","children":[{"id":"91","parent":"90","text":"Consolidación anterior → signo del fragmento (fractal sign)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"92","parent":"90","text":"Tissue-like sign → hepatización pulmonar","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"93","parent":"90","text":"SUGIERE → NEUMONÍA con consolidación extensa","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"94","parent":"90","text":"Broncograma aéreo dinámico → confirma neumonía vs atelectasia [→ M1.4]","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"95","parent":"63","text":"PERFIL A sin sliding\\N(A'-profile)","guid":"THzmTlEtXJgyaMKC4Z5AOw","children":[{"id":"96","parent":"95","text":"Líneas A + deslizamiento pleural ABOLIDO + lung point","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"97","parent":"95","text":"SUGIERE → NEUMOTÓRAX [→ M1.5]","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"98","parent":"95","text":"Rendimiento → S 81%, E 100% (lung point)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"99","parent":"95","text":"Sin lung point → considerar pleurodesis, adherencias, apnea","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"100","parent":"0","text":"COMPONENTE\\NVENOSO DEL BLUE","guid":"cG6dtK1IAKu-ypLG2FbiCA","children":[{"id":"101","parent":"100","text":"ANÁLISIS TVP integrado en el protocolo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"102","parent":"100","text":"Zonas\\Nevaluadas","guid":"lyxCn3gNWcm6YKcrhxIFfg","children":[{"id":"103","parent":"102","text":"Vena yugular interna","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"104","parent":"102","text":"Vena subclavia","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"105","parent":"102","text":"Venas ilio-femoro-poplíteas","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"106","parent":"102","text":"Si posible → VCI y venas de pantorrilla","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"107","parent":"100","text":"Técnica → compresibilidad venosa [→ M6.1]","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"108","parent":"100","text":"PERFIL A + TVP → TROMBOEMBOLISMO PULMONAR","guid":"","children":[{"id":"109","parent":"108","text":"S 81%, E 99% para TEP [→ M2.7]","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"110","parent":"108","text":"BLUE-protocol → evalúa TVP sin necesidad de ecocardiografía","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"111","parent":"0","text":"ARBOL DE DECISIÓN\\N(decision tree)","guid":"7ETt7yKtfaF1sOQuXuVNVA","children":[{"id":"112","parent":"111","text":"PASO 1 → verificar\\Ndeslizamiento pleural anterior","guid":"2EC81IbUNAkn3BwdCqB36A","children":[{"id":"113","parent":"112","text":"Presente → descarta neumotórax → ir a paso 2","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"114","parent":"112","text":"Ausente → perfil A' → buscar lung point → neumotórax [→ M1.5]","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"115","parent":"111","text":"PASO 2 → buscar líneas B\\Nanteriores difusas","guid":"vR7gOIsA1XinDEYnNSAUPw","children":[{"id":"116","parent":"115","text":"B+ bilateral con sliding → perfil B → edema pulmonar","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"117","parent":"115","text":"B+ bilateral sin sliding → perfil B' → neumonía","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"118","parent":"111","text":"PASO 3 → si líneas A\\Npredominantes (perfil A)","guid":"HdPlj8zO5PWsw-1VJX7iqA","children":[{"id":"119","parent":"118","text":"Buscar PLAPS","guid":"","children":[{"id":"120","parent":"119","text":"PLAPS presente → perfil A-PLAPS → neumonía","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"121","parent":"119","text":"PLAPS ausente → buscar TVP","guid":"","children":[{"id":"122","parent":"121","text":"TVP presente → TEP [→ M2.7]","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"123","parent":"121","text":"TVP ausente → perfil A puro → EPOC/asma probable","guid":"","children":[]}]}]}]},{"id":"124","parent":"111","text":"PASO 4 → verificar consolidación anterior","guid":"","children":[{"id":"125","parent":"124","text":"Presente → perfil C → neumonía","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"126","parent":"111","text":"PASO 5 → patrones mixtos (A/B)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"127","parent":"126","text":"Asimetría → neumonía probable","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"128","parent":"0","text":"RENDIMIENTO DIAGNÓSTICO\\NPOR PATOLOGÍA","guid":"v2T-iqAYIgltbTMJ2mdAOA","children":[{"id":"129","parent":"128","text":"EDEMA PULMONAR\\NCARDIOGÉNICO (n=64)","guid":"iVRLVe51T1X2yhwXptwnoQ","children":[{"id":"130","parent":"129","text":"Perfil B → S 97%, E 95%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"131","parent":"129","text":"Diagnóstico más preciso del protocolo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"132","parent":"129","text":"⭐ Correlación con PAOP >18 mmHg [→ M3.2]","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"133","parent":"128","text":"EPOC / ASMA (n=83 →\\N34 asma + 49 EPOC)","guid":"iAk4htu9q7ibcJJ-IFsD2g","children":[{"id":"134","parent":"133","text":"Perfil A → S 89%, E 97%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"135","parent":"133","text":"Diagnóstico POR EXCLUSIÓN → no hay signo positivo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"136","parent":"133","text":"La ecografía descarta otras causas → queda EPOC/asma","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"137","parent":"128","text":"NEUMONÍA\\N(n=83)","guid":"zRbaV6RahyDdEj0H64fwtg","children":[{"id":"138","parent":"137","text":"Perfiles múltiples → A/B, B', C, A+PLAPS","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"139","parent":"137","text":"S 89%, E 94% (combinados)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"140","parent":"137","text":"Metaanálisis 2022 → S pooled 84% (IC 76-89%), E 98% (IC 93-99%)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"141","parent":"140","text":"Ref: Asmara OD et al. Acta Med Indones. 2022;54(2):266-282","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"142","parent":"128","text":"TROMBOEMBOLISMO\\NPULMONAR (n=21)","guid":"kkMMzo0P8rPKji9OTvVw-A","children":[{"id":"143","parent":"142","text":"Perfil A + TVP → S 81%, E 99%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"144","parent":"142","text":"Sin ecocardiografía → limitación para signos directos VD [→ M2.7]","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"145","parent":"128","text":"NEUMOTÓRAX\\N(n=9)","guid":"zoQRVvuQC2h0eB0R-kp-EA","children":[{"id":"146","parent":"145","text":"Perfil A' + lung point → S 81%, E 100%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"147","parent":"145","text":"Lung point patognomónico [→ M1.5]","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"148","parent":"0","text":"VALIDACIONES\\NEXTERNAS","guid":"TH1LihKE04ieAo0NYIdFuQ","children":[{"id":"149","parent":"148","text":"Cremonese 2013 → n=42,\\Nedad media 73a, APACHE II 20","guid":"CY0jB2WgswDvqPuKc2fodg","children":[{"id":"150","parent":"149","text":"Correlación positiva 83.78%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"151","parent":"149","text":"Edema → S 85%, E 86%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"152","parent":"149","text":"Neumonía → S 88%, E 90%","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"153","parent":"148","text":"Singh 2022 (India)\\N→ n=130","guid":"_b3an4N0NOco0F56w29Ebg","children":[{"id":"154","parent":"153","text":"Edema → S 100%, E 94%, precisión 95.38%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"155","parent":"153","text":"Neumonía (combinada) → S 94.11%, E 93.93%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"156","parent":"153","text":"SDRA → B bilateral + consolidación → E 99%","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"157","parent":"148","text":"Metaanálisis Asmara 2022\\N→ 4 estudios","guid":"1u6u0woRQRT1g-u2aa72Mw","children":[{"id":"158","parent":"157","text":"Neumonía → S pooled 84%, E 98%, DOR 252","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"159","parent":"157","text":"Edema → S pooled 89%, E 94%, DOR alto","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"160","parent":"148","text":"LIMITACIONES\\Nde validaciones","guid":"-jdhjE9a7JhWErGCHUTVrg","children":[{"id":"161","parent":"160","text":"Muestras pequeñas","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"162","parent":"160","text":"Exclusión de diagnósticos raros (<2%)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"163","parent":"160","text":"Solo 2 operadores en estudio original → sesgo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"164","parent":"160","text":"No validado en diagnósticos múltiples simultáneos","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"165","parent":"0","text":"RELACIÓN BLUE →\\NFALLS PROTOCOL [→ M11.4]","guid":"MolHiZ0W75gD8zzK0LTx_w","children":[{"id":"166","parent":"165","text":"FALLS = Fluid Administration Limited by Lung Sonography","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"167","parent":"165","text":"Derivado DIRECTO\\Ndel BLUE","guid":"Y2lGpNmgfTvsmTP84Y7d0w","children":[{"id":"168","parent":"167","text":"Ref: Lichtenstein DA. Chest. 2015;147(6):1659-1670","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"169","parent":"167","text":"Ref: Lichtenstein DA, Bar S. Ann Intensive Care. 2024;14:88","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"170","parent":"165","text":"CONCEPTO → diagnóstico\\NSECUENCIAL del shock","guid":"lYmI2kLucHQJ3Kn_ywZYNw","children":[{"id":"171","parent":"170","text":"Paso 1 → eco cardíaca simple → descartar taponamiento, TEP","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"172","parent":"170","text":"Paso 2 → evaluar pulmón → B-lines difusas → shock cardiogénico","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"173","parent":"170","text":"Paso 3 → si A-lines → no cardiogénico → administrar fluidos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"174","parent":"170","text":"Paso 4 → monitorizar A → B transition\\N→ FALLS-endpoint","guid":"URZn_CgKjOtDtT5wcvGduQ","children":[{"id":"175","parent":"174","text":"Aparición de B-lines = sobrecarga → DETENER fluidos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"176","parent":"174","text":"Transición A→B = marcador DIRECTO de volemia clínica","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"177","parent":"165","text":"FALLS-responder → paciente con A-lines que recibe fluidos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"178","parent":"165","text":"Si NO mejora + aparecen B-lines → shock DISTRIBUTIVO (sepsis)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"179","parent":"165","text":"Clasificación Weil → obstructivo → cardiogénico → hipovolémico → distributivo","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"180","parent":"0","text":"BLUE EN EL ANCIANO →\\NCONSIDERACIONES GERIÁTRICAS","guid":"8HayrDooo2gZ7d0KLNIHHw","children":[{"id":"181","parent":"180","text":"MAYOR prevalencia de\\Ndiagnósticos mixtos","guid":"0xsVmNIprre7C6d1cUvXwg","children":[{"id":"182","parent":"181","text":"IC descompensada + neumonía → solapamiento perfiles B y C","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"183","parent":"181","text":"EPOC + neumonía → perfil A basal puede enmascarar B-lines","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"184","parent":"181","text":"Pluripatología → reduce precisión del perfil único","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"185","parent":"180","text":"LÍNEAS B BASALES\\Nen anciano","guid":"gMr03lw19HqaCkbPO9q5DA","children":[{"id":"186","parent":"185","text":"Fibrosis pulmonar basal → B-lines crónicas → confunsor [→ M1.1]","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"187","parent":"185","text":"IC crónica compensada → B-lines focales → no siempre agudo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"188","parent":"185","text":"SOLUCIÓN → comparar con eco previa si disponible","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"189","parent":"180","text":"DESLIZAMIENTO\\NPLEURAL","guid":"wb8LGH-4RPOpg9rjPK7Edg","children":[{"id":"190","parent":"189","text":"Adherencias pleurales → sliding abolido SIN neumotórax","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"191","parent":"189","text":"Más frecuente en anciano con antecedente pleural","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"192","parent":"189","text":"Buscar SIEMPRE lung pulse [→ M1.1] antes de diagnosticar neumotórax","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"193","parent":"180","text":"COMPONENTE\\NVENOSO","guid":"jSnZwyHKIDsOuHLjN4C6xw","children":[{"id":"194","parent":"193","text":"TVP más frecuente en anciano hospitalizado [→ M6.1]","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"195","parent":"193","text":"Inmovilidad, fragilidad, neoplasias ocultas → riesgo aumentado","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"196","parent":"193","text":"Incluir SIEMPRE búsqueda TVP en anciano disneico","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"197","parent":"180","text":"ESCENARIO TÍPICO\\NGERIÁTRICO","guid":"bQZu7fob76zehdFoVqzcFA","children":[{"id":"198","parent":"197","text":"Anciano 82a, frágil (CFS 6), disnea aguda en urgencia","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"199","parent":"197","text":"BLUE → perfil B bilateral → edema probable","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"200","parent":"197","text":"PERO → si fiebre + perfil B asimétrico → considerar neumonía [→ M1.4]","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"201","parent":"197","text":"BLUE + ecocardio focalizada → COMPLEMENTO necesario [→ M2.2]","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"202","parent":"180","text":"NEUMONÍA ASPIRATIVA\\N[→ M1.7]","guid":"GAuOy8_i0hzjculVfbLSmA","children":[{"id":"203","parent":"202","text":"Consolidación posterior + broncograma aéreo → perfil A+PLAPS","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"204","parent":"202","text":"Frecuente en anciano con disfagia, demencia, ACV","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"205","parent":"202","text":"Distribución gravitacional → lóbulos inferiores bilaterales","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"206","parent":"0","text":"LIMITACIONES DEL\\NPROTOCOLO BLUE","guid":"efzNsU7-2KVYtj_MpoKc_Q","children":[{"id":"207","parent":"206","text":"Diagnósticos RAROS (<2%) → excluidos del estudio original","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"208","parent":"206","text":"Diagnósticos MÚLTIPLES SIMULTÁNEOS → no contemplados","guid":"","children":[{"id":"209","parent":"208","text":"Problema MAYOR en geriátricos → pluripatología es la regla","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"210","parent":"206","text":"NO EVALÚA etiología cardíaca → solo descarta por perfil","guid":"","children":[{"id":"211","parent":"210","text":"Complementar con eco cardíaca focalizada [→ M2.1, M2.2]","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"212","parent":"206","text":"CURVA DE\\NAPRENDIZAJE","guid":"ZJ4dmXeXjuULDNzUwT7pQw","children":[{"id":"213","parent":"212","text":"Requiere dominio de 10 signos fundamentales","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"214","parent":"212","text":"Competencia → ~25 exámenes supervisados","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"215","parent":"212","text":"Variabilidad interoperador → limitada con entrenamiento","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"216","parent":"206","text":"NO REEMPLAZA\\Njuicio clínico","guid":"1XUE70y-CMpm8pl6wC8jLg","children":[{"id":"217","parent":"216","text":"Protocolo ORIENTADOR → no confirmatorio","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"218","parent":"216","text":"Siempre correlacionar con clínica, laboratorio, imágenes","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"219","parent":"0","text":"IMPLEMENTACIÓN\\NPRÁCTICA","guid":"n-vxkCQ1fMJ-3uS3h5AqoA","children":[{"id":"220","parent":"219","text":"EQUIPO","guid":"","children":[{"id":"221","parent":"220","text":"Transductor microconvexo IDEAL (permite pulmón + venas + corazón)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"222","parent":"220","text":"Alternativa → convexo + lineal (2 sondas)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"223","parent":"220","text":"Equipo sin Doppler → suficiente para BLUE básico","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"224","parent":"220","text":"Modo B + Modo M → herramientas mínimas necesarias [→ M0.4]","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"225","parent":"219","text":"TIEMPO DE\\NEJECUCIÓN","guid":"zNXmMBexsfcPgQwmblMJuA","children":[{"id":"226","parent":"225","text":"<3 minutos para protocolo completo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"227","parent":"225","text":"Entrenado → <90 segundos (pulmón anterior bilateral)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"228","parent":"219","text":"ESCENARIOS\\NDE USO","guid":"AQ5SKUec8vQTNRmaUu1CpQ","children":[{"id":"229","parent":"228","text":"Urgencia → primer contacto con paciente disneico","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"230","parent":"228","text":"UCI → ingreso con IRA","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"231","parent":"228","text":"Prehospital → triaje rápido (equipos portátiles)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"232","parent":"228","text":"Domicilio geriátrico → ADG con equipo portátil [→ M10.4]","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"233","parent":"219","text":"INTEGRACIÓN CON\\NOTROS PROTOCOLOS","guid":"nLPLc0y7VxlUTvlagjv74w","children":[{"id":"234","parent":"233","text":"RUSH → BLUE como componente tanque [→ M4.2]","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"235","parent":"233","text":"FALLS → extensión para shock [→ M11.4]","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"236","parent":"233","text":"FATE → complemento cardíaco [→ M11.3]","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"237","parent":"233","text":"VExUS → extensión congestiva [→ M11.5]","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"238","parent":"0","text":"Perlas Clínicas ⭐","guid":"","children":[{"id":"239","parent":"238","text":"Perfil B bilateral simétrico = edema pulmonar hasta demostrar lo contrario (S 97%)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"240","parent":"238","text":"Perfil A NO diagnostica EPOC → descarta las demás causas y queda EPOC/asma por exclusión","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"241","parent":"238","text":"SIEMPRE buscar TVP en perfil A sin otra causa → TEP es el diagnóstico oculto","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"242","parent":"238","text":"Lung point = PATOGNOMÓNICO de neumotórax → si lo ves, confía [→ M1.5]","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"243","parent":"238","text":"B-lines + sliding abolido (B') = neumonía, NO edema → el sliding marca la diferencia","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"244","parent":"238","text":"PLAPS-point → la zona más olvidada y más rentable → neumonías ocultas posteriores","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"245","parent":"238","text":"<3 minutos → BLUE es MÁS RÁPIDO que pedir una Rx de tórax en urgencia","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"246","parent":"238","text":"Broncograma aéreo dinámico diferencia neumonía de atelectasia reabsortiva [→ M1.4]","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"247","parent":"238","text":"En anciano disneico → SIEMPRE hacer BLUE antes de radiografía","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"248","parent":"0","text":"Perlas Prácticas\\NIntermodulares ⭐⭐","guid":"ITE0QCIee4WUIm-MS1WjBQ","children":[{"id":"249","parent":"248","text":"Anciano UCI con disnea post-extubación → BLUE seriado cada 6h → detecta transición A→B precoz (edema de reexpansión o WiPO) [→ M7.2, M7.3]","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"250","parent":"248","text":"Perfil B + VCI dilatada no colapsable → IC descompensada confirmada → iniciar diurético ANTES de Rx [→ M2.5, M1.6]","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"251","parent":"248","text":"Paciente frágil (CFS >=5) con perfil A + PLAPS bilateral → neumonía aspirativa es primera causa en anciano con disfagia [→ M1.7, M10.1]","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"252","parent":"248","text":"BLUE en preoperatorio de Fx cadera → perfil B = postergar cirugía hasta optimizar volemia → evaluar con eco cardíaca [→ M10.2, M2.2]","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"253","parent":"248","text":"Transición A→B durante resucitación con fluidos = FALLS-endpoint → DETENER cristaloides → reevaluar vasopresores [→ M11.4, M3.7]","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"254","parent":"248","text":"Anciano ADG con disnea + bilateral B-lines → iniciar furosemida EV y derivar → eco portátil permite diagnóstico domiciliario [→ M10.4]","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"255","parent":"248","text":"Perfil A + TVP en anciano postrado = TEP hasta demostrar lo contrario → anticoagular según riesgo-beneficio geriátrico [→ M6.1, M2.7]","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"256","parent":"248","text":"BLUE normal (perfil A puro, sin PLAPS, sin TVP) en anciano disneico → considerar causas no pulmonares → anemia, acidosis metabólica, ansiedad, sarcopenia diafragmática [→ M7.1, M8.1]","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"257","parent":"248","text":"Score VExUS como extensión del perfil B → si B-lines + congestión venosa sistémica → daño de órgano blanco por congestión [→ M3.6, M11.5]","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"258","parent":"0","text":"Referencias","guid":"","children":[{"id":"259","parent":"258","text":"1. Lichtenstein DA, Mezière GA. Relevance of lung ultrasound in the diagnosis of acute respiratory failure: the BLUE protocol. Chest. 2008;134(1):117-125.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"260","parent":"258","text":"2. Lichtenstein DA. BLUE-protocol and FALLS-protocol: two applications of lung ultrasound in the critically ill. Chest. 2015;147(6):1659-1670.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"261","parent":"258","text":"3. Lichtenstein DA. The BLUE-points: three standardized points used in the BLUE-protocol. Crit Ultrasound J. 2011;3:109-110.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"262","parent":"258","text":"4. Lichtenstein DA, Karakitsos D. Integrating lung ultrasound in the hemodynamic evaluation of acute circulatory failure (the FALLS-protocol). J Crit Care. 2012;27(5):533.e11-19.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"263","parent":"258","text":"5. Lichtenstein DA, Bar S. Lung ultrasound for causal diagnosis of shock (FALLS-protocol). Ann Intensive Care. 2024;14:88.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"264","parent":"258","text":"6. Asmara OD, Pitoyo CW, Wulani V, et al. Accuracy of BLUE protocol to diagnose the cause of ARDS: a meta-analysis. Acta Med Indones. 2022;54(2):266-282.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"265","parent":"258","text":"7. Dexheimer Neto FL, Dalcin PTR, Teixeira C, et al. Validation of a lung ultrasound protocol in acute respiratory failure. Crit Care. 2013;17(Suppl 2):P147.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"266","parent":"258","text":"8. Volpicelli G, Elbarbary M, Blaivas M, et al. International evidence-based recommendations for point-of-care lung ultrasound. Intensive Care Med. 2012;38(4):577-591.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"267","parent":"258","text":"9. Lichtenstein DA, Mezière GA. A-lines and B-lines: lung ultrasound as a bedside tool for predicting PAOP in the critically ill. Chest. 2009;136(4):1014-1020.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"268","parent":"258","text":"10. Ray P, Birolleau S, Lefort Y, et al. Acute respiratory failure in the elderly: etiology, emergency diagnosis and prognosis. Crit Care. 2006;10(3):R82.","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},"node_count":268,"relations":[],"cross_references":[],"specialty":"General","folder":"Entidades clínicas/General","filename":"M1 2 Protocolo BLUE iPad","id":"map_808","resolved_references":[],"title_raw":"M1 2 Protocolo BLUE iPad"}